    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.001 G 29/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Ministers have been invited to be present at the reception of the King’s body
                    at the Piraeus March 26, 3 p.m. The funeral will take place on April second.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
